It's me, dad.

00:03:17.670 --> 00:03:19.120
Something, when you know it,

00:03:20.690 --> 00:03:23.040
might take all your
happiness away.

00:03:44.610 --> 00:03:45.610
Remember!

00:03:48.600 --> 00:03:49.480
Hello?

00:03:50.480 --> 00:03:51.280
Hello?

00:03:51.960 --> 00:03:52.840
Can you hear me?

00:03:54.560 --> 00:03:55.440
Hello?

00:03:55.950 --> 00:03:57.800
Can you hear me?

00:03:58.270 --> 00:03:59.160
Dad.

00:04:00.560 --> 00:04:01.400
Hello?

00:04:01.600 --> 00:04:02.600
Alan?

00:04:03.840 --> 00:04:04.400
Is that you?

00:04:04.410 --> 00:04:05.340
Who exactly are you?

00:04:05.360 --> 00:04:06.320
Alan, calm down.

00:04:06.900 --> 00:04:07.900
Where are you?

00:04:08.160 --> 00:04:09.120
How did you call me?

00:04:09.210 --> 00:04:10.180
Calm down, Alan.

00:04:10.200 --> 00:04:11.240
What's going on?

00:04:11.840 --> 00:04:13.080
Where are you now?

00:04:13.890 --> 00:04:14.880
Calm down?

00:04:15.730 --> 00:04:17.600
My father has died,

00:04:17.730 --> 00:04:19.329
it is stated in the medical record!

00:04:19.360 --> 00:04:20.320
Alan.

00:04:20.910 --> 00:04:21.959
Calm down.

00:04:22.360 --> 00:04:23.440
Who exactly am I?

00:04:23.450 --> 00:04:24.720
Listen to me first.

00:04:25.000 --> 00:04:26.400
- Who the hell am I?
- Wait! Alan.

00:04:26.410 --> 00:04:27.480
Hear me out!

00:04:28.430 --> 00:04:30.050
- A clone?
- Where are you?

00:04:30.080 --> 00:04:30.840
Take it easy.

00:04:30.870 --> 00:04:31.910
Am I a clone?

00:04:31.930 --> 00:04:32.780
Calm down.

00:04:32.780 --> 00:04:34.380
How many clones
have been created?

00:04:34.400 --> 00:04:35.770
How many times
has this happened?

00:04:35.800 --> 00:04:38.320
- Alan, listen to me.
- Tell me what this is all about!

00:04:38.330 --> 00:04:39.409
Tell me!

00:04:39.440 --> 00:04:40.530
There, get him!

00:04:40.560 --> 00:04:41.090
Quick!

00:04:41.120 --> 00:04:42.760
Tell me, hurry!

00:04:42.800 --> 00:04:43.800
Tell me!

00:04:45.150 --> 00:04:46.150
Get him out!

00:04:46.280 --> 00:04:47.010
Let go!

00:04:47.130 --> 00:04:48.040
I said let go!

00:04:49.430 --> 00:04:50.330
Take him back to his room now.

00:04:50.360 --> 00:04:51.310
Yes, Doctor Nil.

00:04:52.159 --> 00:04:53.520
Pete, Doctor Nil,

00:04:55.070 --> 00:04:56.520
Both of you.

00:04:56.640 --> 00:04:57.909
Let go of me!

00:04:57.940 --> 00:04:58.640
Release me!

00:04:59.960 --> 00:05:01.200
Stop causing trouble.

00:05:02.080 --> 00:05:03.240
Please cooperate.

00:05:05.480 --> 00:05:06.730
Alan, calm down.

00:05:06.760 --> 00:05:08.040
Let's get you back
to the room, alright?

00:05:08.540 --> 00:05:09.440
Alan.

00:05:10.140 --> 00:05:11.310
Alan, calm yourself down.

00:05:11.330 --> 00:05:12.160
ALAN!

00:05:14.120 --> 00:05:15.070
Hold him still.

00:05:17.090 --> 00:05:17.890
Let go!

00:05:17.920 --> 00:05:18.920
Hold him.

00:05:20.860 --> 00:05:21.620
Let go!

00:05:21.650 --> 00:05:22.400
Let go, damn it.

00:05:22.740 --> 00:05:23.960
I'm a clone, right?

00:05:24.060 --> 00:05:26.080
- Which number of clone am I?
- Stop talking nonsense!

00:05:34.920 --> 00:05:36.600
Please don't do
this to me, Doctor.

00:05:37.120 --> 00:05:38.120
Let me go.

00:05:48.190 --> 00:05:49.120
Doctor Nil.

00:05:49.370 --> 00:05:51.159
I feel like things are starting
to get out of hand now.

00:05:57.350 --> 00:05:58.640
The time has come.

00:06:11.680 --> 00:06:12.560
Alan.

00:06:15.850 --> 00:06:16.960
Alan.

00:06:27.670 --> 00:06:28.840
With me, Pete.

00:06:29.700 --> 00:06:31.560
Get up slowly, Alan.

00:06:32.280 --> 00:06:33.280
Easy there.

00:06:36.100 --> 00:06:37.560
Can you recall anything
about last night?

00:06:41.270 --> 00:06:42.320
Last night?

00:06:45.240 --> 00:06:46.520
Last night...

00:06:55.350 --> 00:06:56.230
Let go!

00:06:56.260 --> 00:06:57.010
Alan!

00:06:57.040 --> 00:06:58.710
- Alan.
- Let go of me.

00:06:58.730 --> 00:06:59.090
Stop!

00:06:59.100 --> 00:07:00.260
- Alan, stop!
- Stop right there.

00:07:00.300 --> 00:07:01.570
Stay where you are, all of you.

00:07:01.600 --> 00:07:02.390
Stop.

00:07:02.680 --> 00:07:03.710
Don't come any closer.

00:07:07.670 --> 00:07:09.280
What've you guys been
scheming against me?

00:07:09.700 --> 00:07:10.320
Tell me right now.

00:07:10.350 --> 00:07:11.200
Take a deep breath, Alan.

00:07:11.220 --> 00:07:13.240
No, you're going to tell me!

00:07:13.830 --> 00:07:15.160
What are you people
up to against me?

00:07:15.950 --> 00:07:17.010
Answer me now.

00:07:17.040 --> 00:07:18.920
Anyway, who are you?

00:07:19.090 --> 00:07:20.280
You're not my dad.

00:07:20.440 --> 00:07:21.520
My father has died.

00:07:21.610 --> 00:07:22.610
Who are you?

00:07:22.910 --> 00:07:23.600
Who the hell are you?

00:07:23.620 --> 00:07:24.920
Just tell me the truth.

00:07:25.280 --> 00:07:26.320
Say it!

00:07:28.830 --> 00:07:30.040
Fuckin' tell me!

00:07:31.320 --> 00:07:33.810
- Do you want to know the whole truth now?
- Sure shit!

00:07:33.830 --> 00:07:36.040
- Tell me right now!
- Please calm down.

00:07:40.300 --> 00:07:42.800
Today, you'll learn the
truth about everything.

00:07:43.360 --> 00:07:44.400
However,

00:07:44.580 --> 00:07:46.320
I will only reveal it to you

00:07:46.680 --> 00:07:47.690
once you're calm

00:07:48.440 --> 00:07:50.480
and actually ready to listen.

00:07:52.800 --> 00:07:54.159
Are you ready, Alan?

00:08:06.400 --> 00:08:07.360
I am ready.

00:08:14.970 --> 00:08:16.560
Then I'll take you somewhere.

00:09:11.240 --> 00:09:12.480
You want to know, do you?

00:09:16.420 --> 00:09:17.720
The truth is in there.

00:09:55.240 --> 00:09:56.440
Greetings, Alan.

00:09:56.940 --> 00:09:58.280
Don't be afraid just yet.

00:09:59.230 --> 00:10:01.040
If you're watching this video right now,

00:10:01.280 --> 00:10:03.640
that means your
condition's been at its worst.

00:10:04.270 --> 00:10:06.040
But first, Allow me to introduce myself.

00:10:06.260 --> 00:10:07.440
My name's Alan.

00:10:08.060 --> 00:10:11.480
Professer Alan Bunnalai.

00:10:11.940 --> 00:10:13.000
I'm a psychiatrist

00:10:13.590 --> 00:10:16.040
and the founder of
this psychiatric hospital

00:10:16.360 --> 00:10:17.960
"Familienhaus."

00:10:19.780 --> 00:10:20.720
And I

00:10:21.460 --> 00:10:22.680
am you.

00:10:29.490 --> 00:10:30.440
What is this?

00:10:35.700 --> 00:10:38.080
I know you might be shocked

00:10:38.850 --> 00:10:41.120
and won't believe what
I'm going to say next,

00:10:42.180 --> 00:10:43.520
But everything is true.

00:10:44.610 --> 00:10:46.040
We're the same person.

00:10:46.840 --> 00:10:48.280
We have Alzheimer's disease.

00:10:49.880 --> 00:10:52.050
What you believe or peceive yourself as

00:10:52.080 --> 00:10:53.250
as a young man

00:10:54.520 --> 00:10:55.400
is actually

00:10:55.890 --> 00:10:57.770
the result of you forgetting
your current identity.

00:10:57.790 --> 00:10:59.240
Eight straight lines.

00:10:59.330 --> 00:11:01.040
Now, what do you see?

00:11:01.260 --> 00:11:02.320
Ant.

00:11:02.790 --> 00:11:03.720
It can't be.

00:11:03.760 --> 00:11:04.760
What is this?

00:11:05.130 --> 00:11:06.130
The disease that we're having

00:11:06.420 --> 00:11:08.520
- What is this?
- causes our memories

00:11:08.750 --> 00:11:09.920
to rewind back

00:11:10.030 --> 00:11:11.480
to the times that we were happy

00:11:12.160 --> 00:11:13.400
and tie us to them.

00:11:16.880 --> 00:11:18.280
How could you die?

00:11:19.200 --> 00:11:21.000
You're in my memories,

00:11:22.450 --> 00:11:24.080
and you'll be there forever.

00:11:26.870 --> 00:11:28.800
Believe me, it's true.

00:11:29.680 --> 00:11:32.000
In those days was the
time you met Darwin.

00:11:33.790 --> 00:11:34.800
The guy

00:11:35.100 --> 00:11:37.680
who liked to climb windows
just to see you all the time.

00:11:39.090 --> 00:11:41.280
He was the one who made you fall in love.

00:11:42.460 --> 00:11:43.920
Darwin was Win?

00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:45.240
You and Win

00:11:45.500 --> 00:11:47.400
grew up in
the orphanage together.

00:11:47.800 --> 00:11:49.440
Both of you had been
best friends since childhood.

00:11:49.660 --> 00:11:50.850
even during the academies,

00:11:50.880 --> 00:11:52.280
you two had to study
at the same place.

00:11:52.440 --> 00:11:54.280
The two of you had been
there through thick and thin,

00:11:54.820 --> 00:11:56.360
sharing experiences and memories

00:11:57.100 --> 00:11:59.240
before your relationship
blossomed into love.

00:11:59.490 --> 00:12:01.080
Even this hospital

00:12:01.550 --> 00:12:03.960
The two of you created it together

00:12:04.270 --> 00:12:06.560
after the abbot had died.

00:12:07.630 --> 00:12:08.880
The two of you

00:12:09.090 --> 00:12:10.050
felt that it was a shame

00:12:10.230 --> 00:12:12.280
that this place
would be destroyed.

00:12:12.640 --> 00:12:14.560
Both of you were very happy,

00:12:15.320 --> 00:12:17.500
spending your lives here
as if it were a second home.

00:12:17.520 --> 00:12:19.120
A home that housed more
than just the two of you,

00:12:19.360 --> 00:12:21.640
but also held another
life that you had adopted.

00:12:22.480 --> 00:12:23.560
His name was

00:12:23.860 --> 00:12:25.200
"Alex."

00:12:25.750 --> 00:12:26.680
Alex?

00:12:31.100 --> 00:12:33.080
You had been promoted to director

00:12:34.130 --> 00:12:35.760
and Win was your soul mate,

00:12:36.690 --> 00:12:37.680
with Alex

00:12:37.910 --> 00:12:40.160
fulfilling joyfulness
for the family.

00:12:42.460 --> 00:12:43.960
Win meant
everything in your life.

00:12:45.350 --> 00:12:47.840
Never a day passed without
his presence by your side.

00:12:49.200 --> 00:12:50.080
Win...

00:12:50.380 --> 00:12:51.960
He loved you from
the bottom of his heart.

00:12:52.980 --> 00:12:54.040
You also felt the
same way about him.

00:12:55.850 --> 00:12:56.960
But today,

00:12:57.810 --> 00:12:59.680
I'll have to tell you the truth.

00:13:00.090 --> 00:13:02.120
Doctor Darwin Bunnalai

00:13:04.070 --> 00:13:05.400
has passed away

00:13:07.660 --> 00:13:09.520
from leukemia.

00:13:20.920 --> 00:13:22.240
You promised

00:13:22.360 --> 00:13:23.580
we wouldn't leave each other.

00:13:23.650 --> 00:13:24.650
I gave you one minute,

00:13:24.680 --> 00:13:26.440
but I haven't heard a
single apology from you.

00:13:26.620 --> 00:13:28.160
Hello, Mister Alan.

00:13:29.090 --> 00:13:30.570
Are you coming down to eat?

00:13:30.720 --> 00:13:31.680
This way.

00:13:33.140 --> 00:13:34.040
Quick.

00:13:35.840 --> 00:13:36.350
Win!

00:13:36.360 --> 00:13:37.980
I've called, but
you didn't answer.

00:13:38.000 --> 00:13:39.120
Don't ever do this again.

00:13:39.270 --> 00:13:40.290
Not cool.

00:13:40.320 --> 00:13:41.760
You've promised, okay?

00:13:44.430 --> 00:13:45.680
But his body

00:13:46.610 --> 00:13:48.040
is still in the cemetery.

00:13:52.840 --> 00:13:53.800
Dad.

00:13:55.720 --> 00:13:56.760
Are you alright?

00:14:09.520 --> 00:14:11.160
Win has passed away?

00:14:15.320 --> 00:14:16.320
It...

00:14:16.400 --> 00:14:17.420
It can't be.

00:14:18.280 --> 00:14:19.360
That's not true!

00:14:19.560 --> 00:14:20.580
I don't believe it.

00:14:21.030 --> 00:14:22.080
I don't belive this!

00:14:23.020 --> 00:14:24.570
I just seen him yesterday,

00:14:24.600 --> 00:14:26.160
we were still together.

00:14:26.400 --> 00:14:28.000
This is a big deal, Win.

00:14:28.350 --> 00:14:30.480
I don't know anything about myself.

00:14:31.370 --> 00:14:32.570
And I must learn the truth.

00:14:32.600 --> 00:14:33.720
How can you be so sure

00:14:33.900 --> 00:14:35.760
that knowing it will
make your life better?

00:14:37.450 --> 00:14:38.580
We'd been doing well together...

00:14:38.600 --> 00:14:40.760
The lies from others
weren't that bad.

00:14:41.020 --> 00:14:42.480
But the lies you told

00:14:42.840 --> 00:14:44.410
were the most agonizing!

00:14:56.620 --> 00:14:57.600
Win...

00:14:58.060 --> 00:14:59.350
who you have seen,

00:14:59.450 --> 00:15:00.090
met,

00:15:00.120 --> 00:15:00.730
This is...

00:15:00.760 --> 00:15:02.080
or touched...

00:15:03.590 --> 00:15:04.660
Why...

00:15:04.700 --> 00:15:06.200
Why wasn't Win

00:15:07.380 --> 00:15:08.920
in the photo with me?

00:15:12.330 --> 00:15:14.720
because your brain created him.

00:15:15.860 --> 00:15:17.040
You're still bound

00:15:17.420 --> 00:15:19.120
by the happiness
you had with him.

00:15:21.080 --> 00:15:23.440
You've been keeping
him existing to this day.

00:15:24.360 --> 00:15:25.600
However, if you
don't believe me...

00:15:26.940 --> 00:15:28.320
Do you notice
the piece of mirror

00:15:29.020 --> 00:15:31.040
beside the bookshelf?

00:15:32.460 --> 00:15:33.720
Try to concentrate

00:15:34.310 --> 00:15:35.600
and carefully gaze into it.

00:15:36.770 --> 00:15:39.200
You'll see the truth through that mirror.

00:15:59.320 --> 00:16:01.840
I'm intentionally
recording this video for you

00:16:02.710 --> 00:16:04.200
on the days I'm still healthy,

00:16:05.180 --> 00:16:06.960
before my condition
deteriorates.

00:16:07.870 --> 00:16:09.120
Finally,

00:16:09.430 --> 00:16:10.720
I wish that you...

00:16:11.320 --> 00:16:12.720
No, we...

00:16:13.630 --> 00:16:15.520
would get through this together,

00:16:16.370 --> 00:16:18.080
like we always have everytime.

00:16:19.330 --> 00:16:20.400
If we're lucky,

00:16:21.270 --> 00:16:23.280
I hope this will be the last time for us.

00:16:25.140 --> 00:16:26.640
Please do remember, Alan.

00:16:27.780 --> 00:16:28.760
Best of luck to you.

00:18:14.540 --> 00:18:16.210
Have I...

00:18:16.240 --> 00:18:17.760
really gone old now?

00:18:18.960 --> 00:18:20.380
Dad.

00:18:43.080 --> 00:18:45.280
I'd like to be alone
for a moment.

00:19:29.860 --> 00:19:31.640
You must have known that knowing the truth

00:19:32.980 --> 00:19:34.320
terrified me the most.

00:19:36.970 --> 00:19:39.200
So you didn't want me to
hurt more than I already did.

00:19:40.730 --> 00:19:41.760
I admit

00:19:42.970 --> 00:19:44.280
I was scared
and frustrated

00:19:45.270 --> 00:19:47.560
that I had to tell myself every day that...

00:19:49.940 --> 00:19:51.240
from now on,

00:19:53.740 --> 00:19:56.280
I would never have
you by my side again.

00:19:58.130 --> 00:19:59.360
You know, Win?

00:20:01.210 --> 00:20:03.120
Just the thought of
it was excruciating.

00:20:04.310 --> 00:20:06.240
But from this day, I won't
be scared of anything.

00:20:07.640 --> 00:20:09.640
Because I've gone through
everything I feared most.

00:20:11.170 --> 00:20:12.600
If you're with me

00:20:13.380 --> 00:20:14.760
right here and right now,

00:20:16.110 --> 00:20:17.360
I want you to

00:20:18.410 --> 00:20:19.760
get over the fear
together with me.

00:20:21.440 --> 00:20:23.200
I want you to no
longer worry about me.

00:20:25.930 --> 00:20:28.000
Nothing can ever hurt me again.

00:20:29.810 --> 00:20:30.960
From now on,

00:20:31.830 --> 00:20:33.480
I will live my life for you.

00:20:36.280 --> 00:20:38.920
I promise I'll come
visit you everyday...

00:20:41.070 --> 00:20:42.520
so you won't ever
be lonely again.

00:20:58.890 --> 00:21:00.520
Have I been doing this many times?

00:21:02.420 --> 00:21:03.360
Four times.

00:21:06.100 --> 00:21:08.080
I told you to do all of this?

00:21:09.800 --> 00:21:10.760
You did.

00:21:12.940 --> 00:21:14.240
You gave us the command

00:21:15.540 --> 00:21:17.720
that every time you had to restart,

00:21:18.630 --> 00:21:19.920
if things had gotten too far,

00:21:21.240 --> 00:21:22.920
we had to show you the video.

00:21:25.430 --> 00:21:26.720
You must have grown tired of me

00:21:27.590 --> 00:21:29.000
over and over again, right.

00:21:31.550 --> 00:21:32.360
Dad.

00:21:34.060 --> 00:21:36.280
Can you really remember me now?

00:21:43.890 --> 00:21:46.360
Everyone of us has been trying
our best to follow your directives

00:21:47.870 --> 00:21:49.120
and has always hoped

00:21:49.810 --> 00:21:51.760
that each time
would be the last.

00:21:55.850 --> 00:21:57.240
Thank you, son.

00:21:57.460 --> 00:21:58.680
Thank you so much.

00:22:00.880 --> 00:22:01.800
Sure, Dad.

00:22:02.180 --> 00:22:03.080
Alan.

00:22:04.130 --> 00:22:05.810
Time for your medication.

00:22:07.740 --> 00:22:09.240
How dare you

00:22:10.250 --> 00:22:11.960
call me by my name?

00:22:13.690 --> 00:22:15.040
I'm your professor.

00:22:24.570 --> 00:22:25.840
Professor...

00:22:27.050 --> 00:22:28.160
Professor, you...

00:22:28.930 --> 00:22:30.400
you remember me now, right?

00:22:30.570 --> 00:22:31.880
Of course,

00:22:32.470 --> 00:22:33.440
you were

00:22:33.610 --> 00:22:35.480
my troublesome
student, you know?

00:22:38.520 --> 00:22:40.940
You're much more
troublesome than me.

00:22:43.600 --> 00:22:45.280
Thank you very much, Doctor.

00:22:45.910 --> 00:22:47.040
Thank you everyone.

00:22:47.760 --> 00:22:49.240
I truly appreciate it.

00:22:52.450 --> 00:22:54.080
But I still have
another question.

00:22:56.110 --> 00:22:57.960
Does Nate actually exists?

00:22:59.420 --> 00:23:00.400
Uh...

00:23:02.070 --> 00:23:03.320
Nate?

00:23:04.990 --> 00:23:06.120
Who's that?

00:23:09.580 --> 00:23:12.400
Does this mean that
I also created Nate?

00:23:15.340 --> 00:23:16.760
I believe so.

00:23:17.670 --> 00:23:20.440
He was probably the person
you created to be your friend,

00:23:20.880 --> 00:23:23.640
similarly to children's
imaginary friends.

00:23:25.400 --> 00:23:27.160
I really was a trouble maker.

00:23:29.000 --> 00:23:30.140
You sure was!

00:23:37.590 --> 00:23:39.120
Today must have
been tough for you, Nil?

00:23:42.440 --> 00:23:43.880
I guess it wasn't just for me.

00:23:46.660 --> 00:23:47.560
Yeah,

00:23:48.370 --> 00:23:49.600
just like every other time.

00:23:50.870 --> 00:23:52.000
But I believed

00:23:53.770 --> 00:23:55.000
that we would get through it

00:23:58.170 --> 00:24:00.280
You're always so positive, huh?

00:24:02.320 --> 00:24:03.880
I'm just the way I am.

00:24:05.800 --> 00:24:08.000
I don't see the
benefits of overthinking...

00:24:08.990 --> 00:24:10.240
